# Event Choice Handler Rules

`handleEventChoice` logic lives in the reducer layer (`rules/events.ts`).
`useEventSystem.ts` dispatches `HANDLE_EVENT_CHOICE` and listens for side effects.

## Pattern

```typescript
// Hook — thin dispatcher
const handleEventChoice = (choiceId: string) => {
  dispatch({ type: 'HANDLE_EVENT_CHOICE', choiceId });
};

// Reducer — all game logic
function reduceHandleEventChoice(state, action, sideEffects) {
  // mutation logic here
}
```

## Do NOT add event resolution logic back into `useEventSystem.ts`

All dungeon event outcomes (stat changes, card rewards, gold changes, equipment changes)
must be resolved in the reducer. The hook only handles:
- Dispatching the chosen option
- Listening for UI side effects (animations, transitions)
